    "summary": "RADBOUDUMC & RADBOUD UNIVERSITY\nKey to my professional practice is building together with artists cross overs between contemporary art, research, other disciplines and cultural domains. My ambition in the Radboudumc | Radboud University is a more included art program. Rather than buying artworks as most corporate art collections do, since 2014 focus is on of the specific knowledge and practices of artists that can change perspectives on things we assume to know. I firmly believe the all over transformation of care, medicine, health and education urgently needs the essentially different, more open and connecting knowledge, repertoire and non-protocol practices of artists. As a consequence of the mind set I initiated, artists are working with patients, doctors, researchers and students on care related issues and concepts. By doing so the program wants to make a significant impact on the formation of personalized health care and on the engagement of contemporary art in urgent societal issues, as well.\n\nGENERAL\nSince 1989 am working as a curator of innovative art projects, art programs and exhibitions: for example in the museum of contemporary art in Gent (Belgium), Susan Wyss Gallery Z\u00fcrich, Sonsbeek 93 (Arnhem, Netherlands), the province Overijssel in the Netherlands. Besides this I published a lot of articles and essays in international catalogues and magazines on contemporary art and architecture. From 1995 till 2001 I was editor in chief of the Dutch magazine on contemporary art Metropolis M. Since September 2013 I am head of the art program of Radboud university medical center (Radboudumc) and Radboud University. \n\nMember of AICA | Association Internationale des Critiques d'Art\nMember of the board of Netherlands Association of Corporate Art Collection\nAwarded for The impact Award 2016\n",
